Heat Map¶

In [9]:
import pandas as pd
import folium
from folium.plugins import HeatMap
def create_density_map(df: pd.DataFrame, radius: float) -> folium.Map:
    """Creates a folium Map object with a heatmap layer representing the density of the points in the DataFrame."""
    # Create the folium map
    density_map = folium.Map(location=[df['lat'].mean(), df['lng'].mean()], zoom_start=14)

    # Convert the DataFrame to a list of coordinates
    points = df[['lat', 'lng']].values.tolist()

    # Create a heatmap layer using the list of coordinates
    heatmap = HeatMap(points,
        name='Points Density',
        radius=radius,
    )

    # Add the heatmap layer to the map
    heatmap.add_to(density_map)

    return density_map

data = hotspots[hotspots["score_v3"] > 0.6]
density_map = create_density_map(data, 15)

Coverage¶

In [11]:
from shapely.geometry import Point
from shapely.ops import unary_union
from shapely.geometry import MultiPolygon
import pyproj

from shapely.geometry import Point
from shapely.ops import transform

wgs84 = pyproj.CRS('EPSG:4326')
utm = pyproj.CRS('EPSG:32618')

def get_polygon_union(longitude: pd.Series, latitude: pd.Series, radius = 15):
    buffer = radius / 100000
    circles = pd.concat([longitude, latitude], axis = 1).apply(lambda row:
        Point(row[longitude.name], row[latitude.name]).buffer(buffer)
    , axis = 1)

    polygon = unary_union(circles.to_list())
    return polygon
In [12]:
data = hotspots

coverage_polygon = get_polygon_union(data["lng"], data["lat"], 100)
print("Area of coverage_polygon:", coverage_polygon.area)


project = pyproj.Transformer.from_crs(wgs84, utm, always_xy=True).transform
coverage_polygon_transformed = transform(project, coverage_polygon)
print("Area of coverage_polygon_transformed:", coverage_polygon_transformed.area)
print("Area of coverage_polygon:", coverage_polygon.area)

cherkasy_polygon_transformed = transform(project, cherkasy_polygon)

print("Area of cherkasy_polygon_transformed:", cherkasy_polygon_transformed.area)
print("Area of cherkasy_polygon:", cherkasy_polygon.area)

print(f"Coverage Rate: {round(coverage_polygon_transformed.area / cherkasy_polygon_transformed.area * 100, 2)} %")
